<subSubSection id="58DC653BFFED0514FF24F819FC5FFF31" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="255" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="107936B0FFED0514FF24F819FC5FFF31" blockId="3.[151,1436,1693,2006]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1435,151,248]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="255" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="22B2EAA2FFED0513FF24F819FEDFF81F" bold="true" box="[199,345,1981,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Distribution</emphasis>
. Widely distributed in the 
<collectingRegion id="D202F852FFED0513FD55F819FC94F81F" box="[694,786,1981,2006]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Oriental</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFED0513FCC8F819FCECF81F" box="[811,874,1981,2006]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">India</collectingCountry>
), Palaearctic (
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFED0513FBF8F81AFBCAF81F" box="[1051,1100,1982,2006]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFED0513FB82F819FA87F81F" box="[1121,1281,1981,2006]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFED0513FAF5F81AFADDF81F" box="[1302,1371,1982,2006]" name="Egypt" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Egypt</collectingCountry>
) and Afrotropical regions (southwards to 
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFEA0514FDA1FF33FD2AFF79" box="[578,684,151,176]" name="Tanzania" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
). Within 
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFEA0514FCFFFF3CFCCFFF66" box="[796,841,152,175]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Iran</collectingCountry>
this 
<taxonomicName id="D7C64D33FFEA0514FC6AFF33FB9DFF79" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1829" box="[905,1051,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22B2EAA2FFEA0514FC6AFF33FB9DFF79" box="[905,1051,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Brachymeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has hitherto been reported from southern 
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFEA0514FEE3FF19FEABFF1D" box="[256,301,189,212]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Iran</collectingCountry>
(Masi 1924, 1951; Lotfalizadeh 
<emphasis id="22B2EAA2FFEA0514FD45FF19FD5EFF1C" box="[678,728,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">et al</emphasis>
. 2012: as 
<taxonomicName id="D7C64D33FFEA0514FCB2FF19FC42FF1D" authorityName="Z. Boucek" baseAuthorityName="Masi" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[849,964,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="22B2EAA2FFEA0514FCB2FF19FC42FF1D" box="[849,964,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">B. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The present record of this species from northern 
<collectingCountry id="68D17620FFEA0514FF1FFF44FEAFFF3E" box="[252,297,224,247]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Iran</collectingCountry>
extends the distribution of this species to the Iranian plateau.
</paragraph>
